'''EA Montreal'''，是[[加拿大|加拿大]]的游戏开发工作室。该工作室设在魁北克[[蒙特利尔|蒙特利尔]]，2004年3月17日由[[美国艺电|美国艺电]]创立<ref name="EAMontrealOpen">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/eas-montreal-studio-open-for-business-6091643|title=EA's Montreal Studio open for business|publisher=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]]|last=Navarro|first=Alex|date=2004-03-17|accessdate=2013-01-26|archive-date=2013-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520072032/http://www.gamespot.com/news/eas-montreal-studio-open-for-business-6091643|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

该工作室由前育碧员工Alain Tascan和BAM! Entertainment总经理成立，该工作室是少数由EA创立的工作室。2006年该工作室收购JAMDAT，JAMDAT在蒙特利尔的办事处搬到了EA Montreal所在地。

EA Montreal和EA Mobile Montreal是分开运营。然而，在2007年，艺电开发工作室分成四部分，EA Montreal成为EA Games品牌（弗兰克Gibeau，总裁）的一部分。EA Montreal与其他EA工作室负责运营Boogie和Army of Two。

The Visceral Montreal studio在2013年2月关闭<ref name="Gameinformer">{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2013/02/21/report-army-of-two-developer-suffers-layoffs.aspx|title=Visceral Montreal Employee Confirms Entire Staff Let Go|last=Marchiafava|first=Jeff|publisher=[[Game_Informer|Game Informer]]|date=2013-02-21|accessdate=2013-03-11|archive-date=2013-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130224024835/http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2013/02/21/report-army-of-two-developer-suffers-layoffs.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2012年4月，EA宣布对移动部门进行裁员。<ref>{{cite web|last=Futter|first=Mike|title=[Updated] "Key Development Studio" EA Montreal's Mobile Division Hit With Layoffs - News - www.GameInformer.com|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2013/04/11/rumor-ea-montreal-mobile-division-hit-with-layoffs.aspx|work=Game Informer|publisher=GameStop Corporation|accessdate=15 September 2013|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924104046/http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2013/04/11/rumor-ea-montreal-mobile-division-hit-with-layoffs.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>2015年2月对移动部门再进行裁员 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/235973/Report_Layoffs_strike_EA_Montreal.php|title=Report: Layoffs strike EA Montreal|author=Alex Wawro|work=[[Gamasutra|Gamasutra]]|date=2015-02-06|accessdate=2015-02-10|archive-date=2015-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210124341/http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/235973/Report_Layoffs_strike_EA_Montreal.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

